FBIS3-35255 "drnes036yy_94002" FBIS-NES-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Arab-Israeli Talks Gaps in Security Talks `Unbridgeable' TA2202192894 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in Hebrew 1800 GMT 22 Feb 94 TA2202192894 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Serious differences of opinion erupted today in the Cairo security talks. An Israeli delegate said today that the gaps in the positions of the sides are unbridgeable and that yet another meeting between Peres and 'Arafat will be needed. Our correspondent Roni Daniyel has learned that Israel rejected the PLO's demand to release all 9,000 Palestinian prisoners. In the Civilian Affairs Committee, on the other hand, significant progress has been reported in most issues.
